<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{kiri}}}} when used as a conjunction means that since something happened, nothing has changed.
When used as a particle, @HI{{@EM{{kiri}}}} indicates a strict limitation of a number or quantity.
</p>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{kkiri}}}} is a more colloquial form that can also be more emphatic.
</p>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
Used after a noun or a verb, @HI{{@EM{{kiri}}}} indicates a "cutting off" point or limit and may be translated as "only".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{anoojiisanha,1@KJ{{person}}@EM{{kiri}}de@KJ{{large}}kina@KJ{{house}}ni@KJ{{dwell}}ndeiru.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      That old man lives all by himself in a big house.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{kiri}}}} emphasises a negative meaning and may be translated as "only".
In this usage it may be replaced by <a href="grammar-particle-dake.html">@HI{{dake}}</a>.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ato@FG{{@KJ{{discharge^car}}:hassha}}made2@KJ{{part}}@EM{{kiri}}dakara,@FG{{@KJ{{mountain^book}}:yamamoto}}sanhatotemo
      @FG{{@KJ{{interval}}:ma}}ni@FG{{@KJ{{fit}}:a}}wanaidarou.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The train leaves in just two minutes, so it's very unlikely that Yamamoto will make it in time.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{kiri}}}} can indicate the most recent incidence of something. In this case it can be translated as "the last".


<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{arann}}sankaraha@KJ{{gone^year}}@KT{{kurisumasu}}@MIDDOT{{}}@KT{{ka-do}}ga@KJ{{come}}ta@EM{{kiri}}de,sonoato@KJ{{hand^paper}}ga@KJ{{come}}masenn.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The last I heard from Alan was a Christmas card last year. Since then no letters have come.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{kore/sore/are}}@HI{{@EM{{kiri}}}}  is used to mean "only this/that much" or "ever since this/that time".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{he}}karahaare@HI{{@EM{{kkiri}}}}@KJ{{what}}mo@FG{{@KJ{{take*along^entwine}}:renraku}}ganaino?}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      You haven't heard anything from him since then?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@Vta{{}}@HI{{@EM{{kiri}}}} is used to mean that ever since someone did something in the past, nothing has changed.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{he^woman}}toha10@KJ{{year}}@FG{{@KJ{{by*means*of^above}}:ijou}}mo@KJ{{in*front}}@KT{{pari}}de@KJ{{meeting}}tta@EM{{kiri}}de,
      sono@FG{{@KJ{{behind}}:go}}doushiteirunoka,@FG{{@KJ{{whole^sort*of*thing}}:zenzen'}}@KJ{{know}}ranai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I haven't seen her since we met in Paris 10 years ago and I have no idea how she's been doing since then.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

